Hi!

I'm having the same problem.

For now I'm using this dirty trick:

```rust
let url = String::from("...");
let res = reqwest::get(url.as_str())
    .and_then(|r| r.error_for_status())
    .map_err(|e| display_http_error(e, url))

fn display_http_error(e: reqwest::Error, url: String) -> String {
    e.to_string().replace(format!("{}: ", url).as_str(), "")
}
```

It works because I still have access to the URL string, but it is not a nice solution...

@dsferruzza what you describe is the same as my first suggestion: have a secondary `Display` returned by a method on `Error`. It'd be usable like this:

```rust
let error = got_some_reqwest_error();

// Output: "http://httpbin.org/redirect/11: Too many redirects"
println!("{}", error);


// Output: "Too many redirects"
println!("{}", error.without_url());
```

> What about fn without_url(&self) -> Cow<Self>? A method of Error which removes url.

I'm assuming the method would return `Cow::Owned` with a clone of the error if the URL was removed? If it is indeed possible to clone `reqwest::Error`, I think it's better to implement the Clone trait for Error and make `without_url` take self by value.

As far as I can tell, these are all viable options (I added the last one).
```rust
/// Remove URL information from error and return modified error
pub fn without_url(self) -> Self;
/// Generate a printable object which shows the error without URL information
pub fn without_url(&self) -> impl Display;
/// Remove URL information from this error
pub fn delete_url(&mut self);
```

Hi all!

I'm coming up against this same issue (with an API key in the query). @seanmonstar /@kangalioo, is there any plan to merge #1299? Otherwise, I'd propose a PR with the following API which probably covers the gamut of the above:
```rust

/// Mutative methods

/// Get a mutable reference to the url, if present (for example, if you wanted to modify the url to remove the sensitive information
pub fn url_mut(&mut self) -> Option<&mut Url>;
/// Remove the url entirely
pub fn clear_url(&mut self) -> &mut Self;
/// Strip the url and return self (similar to `clear_url`, but possibly more ergonomic in some cases)
pub fn without_url(mut self) -> Self;

/// Format Structs (where each return wrapper implements Display)

/// Return a wrapper struct (borrowing self) that masks the url in the display impl (but still shows that it exists
pub fn as_url_masked(&self) -> UrlMaskedError<'_>;
/// Return a wrapper struct (borrowing self) that ignores the url field
pub fn as_url_hidden(&self) -> UrlHiddenError<'_>;
/// Return a wrapper struct (borrowing self) that applies a custom formatting function to the url on display.
pub fn with_url_formatter<F: Fn(&Url, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter) -> std::fmt::Result>(&self, f: F) -> UrlFormattedError<'_, F>;

```

And, since we're allowing mutation of the `url` field, it may make sense to make `Error::with_url`, which already exists, public.
